snippet.textDisplay: I'd love to see you guys do a whole video about the various generations of Godzilla films and the special effects involved. The way I'd like to see you do it is to look at at least one or two films from each era and talk about the evolution of the effects used to create the King of the Monsters. You could start with the 'Showa' period, breaking down how they pioneered the 'suitmation' of the original 1954 Godzilla movie, then maybe talk a little bit about the final battle in 'Destroy All Monsters', which was one of Toho's biggest and most complicated effects scenes of the time. Then you move on to the 'Heisei' era in the 1990's and talk about how they improved and added to the technology, perhaps using effects shots from 'Godzilla vs King Ghidorah' as an example. Another shot from this era you could look at is the scene of Godzilla being frozen in 'Godzilla vs Destoroyah'. You already did a video on the 1998 American Godzilla, but you could still do a scene about it if you want just for a quick comparison. Next is the 'Millenium' series, and two of the films I'd like you to look at from that era would be 'Godzilla Against MechaGodzilla' and 'Godzilla: Final Wars'. For the last segment you would of course compare the effects in the most recent American film, 'Godzilla: King of the Monsters'.
